      "body" : "> To make sure my transactions is mined in the very next block, I pay a very high fee. With ANYONECANPAY everyone want to mix their coins will freeride my transaction by adding dust inputs.\r\n\r\nIs that so bad?  The miner will either choose the newly updated transaction, or it won't?  It's only an issue if the miner isn't considering all previously known versions of the transaction,  not just replacing the old with the new.",
